
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class University {
    +String name
    +List<Faculty> faculties
}

class Faculty {
    +String name
    +Employee dean
    +University university
}

class Institute {
    +String name
    +Address address
    +Faculty faculty
}

class Address {
    +String street
    +String city
    +String postalCode
}

class Employee {
    +int ssn
    +String name
    +String email
    +University university
    +int totalEmployees
}

abstract class StaffType {
}

class ResearchStaff extends StaffType {
}

class AdministrativeStaff extends StaffType {
}

class ResearchAssistant {
    +String fieldOfResearch
    +List<Project> projects
    +List<Course> coursesTaught
    +Institute institute
    +StaffType staffType
}

class Project {
    +String name
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate
    +int hoursAssigned
    +ResearchAssistant ra
}

class Course {
    +String id
    +String name
    +int weeklyHours
    +ResearchAssistant lecturer
}

' Define relationships

University "1" *-- "many" Faculty : has
Faculty "1" *-- "many" Institute : contains
Faculty "1" --> "1" Employee : headed by
Employee "many" ..> "1" University : belongs to

Institute "1" --> "many" ResearchAssistant : assigns
ResearchAssistant "many" ..> "1" Institute : assigned to

Employee "many" ..|> "1" StaffType : has type
ResearchAssistant "1" ..|> "1" StaffType : as

ResearchAssistant "many" *-- "many" Project : involved in
Project "many" ..> "1" ResearchAssistant : involves

ResearchAssistant "many" *-- "many" Course : teaches
Course "many" ..> "1" ResearchAssistant : taught by

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:
- **University**, **Faculty**, and **Institute** form a hierarchical structure.
- Each **Faculty** has one **Dean** (an `Employee`).
- **Employees** are categorized into **ResearchStaff** and **AdministrativeStaff**.
- **ResearchAssistants** can be assigned to an **Institute**, participate in **Projects**, and teach **Courses**.
- **Courses** are uniquely identified and linked to **Lecturers** (RAs who teach).
- The diagram uses UML syntax for inheritance (`..|>`), associations (`-->`, `*--`), and composition where appropriate.

